s://zenodo.org/record/6467456/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6467460/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6467462/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6467466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF27BFAF0EDA7FA8F" box="[877,919,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">1–6</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF55FFAF0EF10FA6F" authority="Mackauer" authorityName="Mackauer" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aphidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF55FFAF0EAFDFA8F" box="[1097,1229,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">A. funebris</emphasis>
Mackauer
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF87FF9CF039FAD0EF56FA6F" box="[303,358,1402,1428]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[168,201,1145,1167]" captionTargetBox="[258,1095,178,1094]" captionTargetId="figure-247@2.[235,1130,166,1111]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Aphidius megourae, ♀ (1–6) and A. funebris, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — head, dorsal aspect; 2, 8 — antenna; 3, 9 — forewing; 4, 10 — propodeum; 5, 11 — petiole; 6, 12 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 2. Aphidius megourae, ♀ (1–6) и A. funebris, ♀ (7–12): 1, 7 — голова, вид сверху; 2, 8 — усик; 3, 9 — переднее крыло; 4, 10 — проподеум; 5, 11 — стебелёк; 6, 12 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449135" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449135/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">fig 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF064FAD0EF9BFA6F" box="[370,427,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF87FF9CF064FAD0EFB0FA6F" box="[370,384,1402,1428]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,205,1723,1745]" captionTargetBox="[534,881,1072,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-347@7.[529,894,1061,1710]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig.7. Pauesia abietis, ♀: 1 — antenna; 2 — mesonotum; 3 — forewing; 4 — propodeum; 5 — petiole; 6 — ovipositor sheath. Рис. 7. Pauesia abietis, ♀: 1 — усик; 2 — среднеспинка; 3 — переднее крыло; 4 — проподеум; 5 — стебелёк; 6 — створки яйцеклада." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449137" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449137/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">7</figureCitation>
–12
</emphasis>
), from which it differs by: 1) more convex temples; 2) antenna with 19–20 segments; 3) narrower and longer central cell (fused1st discal, 1st and 2nd submarginal cells) of forewing; 4) narrower areola on propodeum; 5) more elongated petiole: 3.6–3.8 times as long as wide at spiracles level; 6) ovipositor sheath less sharp and almost not thinned at apex; 7) host range.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF87FF9CF1C9F9B1ED58F96E" blockId="2.[170,1229,1338,1845]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
H o s t s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF052F9B1EFC4F9CF" authorityName="Buckton" authorityYear="1876" box="[324,500,1563,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Megoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viciae">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF052F9B1EFC4F9CF" box="[324,500,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Megoura viciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF336F9B0ECC4F9CF" box="[544,756,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lathyrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF336F9B0ECC4F9CF" box="[544,756,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Lathyrus pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF23BF9B1ED8AF9CF" box="[813,954,1563,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cracca">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF23BF9B1ED8AF9CF" box="[813,954,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Vicia cracca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the main host (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF87FF9CF59EF9B0EED5F9AE" author="Stary, P." pageId="2" pageNumber="389" pagination="187 - 227" refId="ref7652" refString="Stary, P. Aphidiid Parasites of Aphids in USSR (Hymenoptera, Aphidiidae) // Acta faun. ent. Mus. Nat. Pragae. - 1965. - 10, N 96. - P. 187 - 227." type="journal article" year="1965">Starý, 1965</bibRefCitation>
, 2006; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF87FF9CF023F990EC01F9AF" author="Tobias, V. I. &amp; Chiriac, I. G." box="[309,561,1594,1620]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" refId="ref7953" refString="Tobias, V. I., Chiriac, I. G. Fam. Aphidiidae / Ed. G. S. Medvedev. - Leningrad: Nauka, 1986. - P. 254. - (Keys to the insects of the European part of the USSR; Vol. 3, part 5). - Russian: Tobiaс V. I., Kiрiik I. G. Сiм. Aphidiidae." type="book" year="1986">Tobias, Chiriac, 1986</bibRefCitation>
; Yu et al., 2012). For a long time 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF2A5F990EA75F9AF" authorityName="Stary" authorityYear="1965" box="[947,1093,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aphidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megourae">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF2A5F990EA75F9AF" box="[947,1093,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">A. megourae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considered being monophagous, but now there are information about its parasitizing on 
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF542F9F0EC30F96F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF542F9F0EF04F96F" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Acyrthosiphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisum">Acyrthosiphon pisum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF056F9D0EC30F96F" box="[320,512,1658,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="craccivora">Aphis craccivora</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF87FF9CF356F9D0ED54F96E" authority="(Yu et al., 2012)" baseAuthorityName="Yu" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[576,868,1658,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabae">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF87FF9CF356F9D0EC91F96F" box="[576,673,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">A. fabae</emphasis>
(Yu et al., 2012)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF87FF9CF1C9F931ED85F92F" blockId="2.[170,1229,1338,1845]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
H a b i t a t s. Wet meadows, clearings in woods and in pathways (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF87FF9CF2CFF930EA51F94E" author="Stary, P." box="[985,1121,1690,1717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" pagination="187 - 227" refId="ref7652" refString="Stary, P. Aphidiid Parasites of Aphids in USSR (Hymenoptera, Aphidiidae) // Acta faun. ent. Mus. Nat. Pragae. - 1965. - 10, N 96. - P. 187 - 227." type="journal article" year="1965">Starý, 1965</bibRefCitation>
), pasture meadows, roadsides (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF87FF9CF0B2F910EC1DF92E" author="Stary, P." box="[420,557,1722,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" refId="ref7855" refString="Stary, P. Aphid parasitoids of the Czech Republic (Hymenoptera: Braconidae, Aphidiinae). - Praha: Academia, 2006. - 430 p." type="book" year="2006">Starý, 2006</bibRefCitation>
), mixed forests: edges and glades.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF87FF9CF1C9F971EF06F8CE" blockId="2.[170,1229,1338,1845]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
